verbose_text: The level of beta-CTX rose to a plateau in stage III after fracture, and then continued to rise to its highest value of 1.1 +/-0.4 ng/mL in stage V. PINP continued to rise after fracture and reached a peak of 81.5 +/-26.77 ng/mL in stage V. ALP started to decrease at the beginning of fracture, then increased rapidly to the highest value of 132.17 +/-40.5 U/L in stage IV (as shown in XREF_TABLE).
